##My mom lost her best friend during the outbreak

Micro signal

Features an introduction to the refreshing flavor of the feminist hardcore

At the beginning of the film Amelie, an old man is erasing his recently deceased friend from his address book. When I first saw this scene, I felt too cold and thin, I think if there is a feeling, the other side of the traces would like to stay! Later, I thought about it and tried to understand: The dead man's phone number is no longer useful, but it's still emotionally unacceptable, at least I don't think I should do it.

But recently, my mom deleted her best friend's Wechat, too. Her best friend died, jumped off a building during a pneumonia quarantine (today is her first seven) .

Perhaps to see this process in person, I would like to think of my initial evaluation how hasty, to really understand, express feelings there is no single or rigid way and sustenance, and sometimes may not even express the space and conditions.

During the epidemic, for example, people were in a panic about being infected, about not having food to eat, about not being able to go out and work and not having income. The time of acceptance and farewell is cut short as the life goes by. In the face of basic health and livelihood security, mourning and ritual seem so extravagant, or no longer important.

Screenshot from the movie Amelie

My home in a county-level city in Hubei, during the outbreak of martial law throughout the city, the last 20 days is the regulation residents can not leave their homes. My mother went from hearing about her friend's death to not talking about it for four days. Four days seems a bit short, and the further it goes, the more unreal it seems that none of this ever happened.

But these four days, I see the emotion is so real, simple and vivid. So I want to write them down: a Lost Life, a friendship, a loss of sadness are all real.

The secret of February 29th

Not long after dinner, I suddenly heard my mother talking loudly on the phone, which is not very common: My mother usually likes to stress at home to keep quiet and not to disturb each other, she usually chat by herself with the door closed. But this time I clearly heard her on the phone repeatedly asking "is it true? " "Is it in s city? "

I went to my mother's open door was about to ask, my mother from the inside, with me to say: "Your Aunt Ding Mei (not her real name) jumped off the building, isolation for 13 days jumped off the building. "

It didn't occur to me for a moment that this was not the name of a close relative, my mom was already explaining to me, "mom's best friend. " (we sometimes put "aunt" after her best friend's name to indicate closeness.).

I did not think that this person and her mother so close, the first reaction is also asked: "How do you know? Is it true? " Her mother said that uncle called her to tell her, she can not be sure. I said Call Aunt ding-mei and we'll find out? But my mother looked a little nervous and said, "I can't do it. ".

Later, she added: "I'll send her a Wechat, right? If she returns it, she's fine, and if she doesn't, it's true, right? " As her mother typed by hand on her phone, she said to herself: "I'll ask: How are you doing? "

To The living room, my mother told the news to father and uncle again: "Ding Mei jumped off the building, isolation for 13 days jumped off the building. " My father and uncle asked what was going on, my mother says she didn't know aunt dimmy had a new coronavirus pneumonia, or that she had returned from g city for the New Year —— as if she was at her son's house in G. Their last contact was before the Lunar New Year.

My uncle had just called to say that aunt dimmy had jumped off a building in a secluded area, and my mother had just found out that she was in S. But the news was known to him through the public security, said not to spread, even her family may not know.
Why did you jump? Did something happen? Why not? We don't even know.

When my father and uncle heard "keep this between us, " they hurriedly told my mother to "never speak out of turn. " They also mentioned that the news on TV often said that people were caught spreading rumors in violation of the law, meaning don't get into trouble, my mother promised, "I won't tell anyone. ".

My mother mentioned that she sent a greeting to aunt Dingmei Wechat, father and uncle think she should not send, said after not to send, mother promised down. And everyone goes about their business.

Later, I made milk tea to ask my mother to drink, my mother said she did not drink. Usually my mother and I are a good (four tone) to eat the man (dialect: refers to a love of food) , during the epidemic often cooked health of sweet soup for us to drink. But this time I brought milk tea to my mother, she was not interested.

I thought my mother had better get a reply from aunt Dimmesdale, and find it a false alarm.

March 1st aunt dimple's friendship with her mother

The next day, I did not get up, I heard my mother in the Living Room with dad and uncle said, aunt Ding Mei's news is true, uncle said has been confirmed, aunt Ding Mei jumped to death on the 28th, people have been cremated.

At lunch, my mother said that she had not slept all night, and that if she slept for a while, she would dream of aunt dimmy. When my mother told this story, she didn't describe her feelings and feelings, as if it were just a statement of ordinary insomnia. I asked my mother did not sleep well should not make up during the day sleep? But Mother did not catch up on sleep, or as usual to do housework.

Mom sent aunt Ding Mei that wechat is certainly not a reply. Father and uncle also told my mother not to tell others, mother said she and who did not take the initiative to mention. "I've deleted her wechat, " she added. I was startled. Think of the old man in Amelie who erased his best friend's phone number.

Screenshot from the movie Amelie

I tried to associate aunt dimmy with the image of my mother's friend, who I remembered, and asked my mother if she had been to our house when I was in junior high. When my father heard this, he answered and said, "she must not be very beautiful. " My mother said, "she is not very ugly either. She is a little black and very clever. " My mother is a little happy, facial expression is no longer like just so wooden, began to cheer up.

Aunt dimmy lived down the street from my grandmother and went to school with my mother, "the best of the best, " she added. She's also a bit of a legend, because she's a known cheater around here. My mother also explained that cheating is playing cards and other partners cheat and so on, I know that I heard right.

My Mom and dad were listening to a novel called the cheat King, and I said, I know, just like in the cheat King. My mother said: "Yes! She is the King of the Card Shark here" , here the Popular Card Shark Routine: What small movements, eye expressions are many of her first invention.

She played cards for her family to make a good living. "otherwise, her husband wouldn't have the money to buy a big house and give her son a down payment in g city with such a small salary, " she said, but my mother still spoke of her friend with some pride, saying, "If she had been smart enough to study, she would have gone to college. " My father and uncle listened and agreed.

Screenshot of God of gamblers

In fact, aunt Ding Mei is not like "God of gamblers" in the movies like gambling, lose money to others lost all that kind of. They win a few hundred bucks at a time, sometimes a few dozen. Her usual routine is: Take a partner female companion go to an acquaintance's house, ask an acquaintance to invite someone to play Mahjong, and then partner to win each other's gambling (up to a few hundred dollars) .

Sometimes aunt Ding Mei's partner asks someone to play Mahjong. My mother told of a time when aunt dimmy had a partner who was a bit pretty, and when a man came up to her in the ballroom dancing, she invited him to play Mahjong with her. The man thinks he has the opportunity, bought a big watermelon to be eager to be gallant, the result on the body all lose money, big: "Get a half day is a female impostor! " (my mother imitates his accent to explain to us, all laughed) .

This kind of routine is a bit like a pyramid scheme, a family acquaintances, friends "visit" down, also know almost all the people have offended, aunt and mother common classmates no one like aunt Dingmei, they were "killed familiar" most of her a lot of resentment.

When my mother mentioned the wife of a male classmate (who was also their classmate) , word came out that "no one will come to the house from now on. ". Because once aunt Ding Mei also went to this male classmate's house to play Mahjong in the old way, but the male classmate called his friend without any money. It was the male classmate who gave them the money to play Mahjong, so all the money that was lost was the male classmate's, they were so angry with her that they cut her off and even blamed the other students.

There are also some people who, although they have not torn aunt Dingmei face to face, will speak ill of aunt Dingmei behind her back. My mother also knows that aunt Dingmei is unreasonable, so it is not easy for others to speak ill of aunt Dingmei in front of her. However, she, she never answers their questions, only saying, "she's smart. ". My mother said: "I don't like to be like them, face to face with you very good, behind your talk you worthless. "

Sometimes when people lose money and get angry, they hit aunt Ding Mei. My mother said, "once she was beaten in the head, and the blood flowed. " But aunt Ding Mei has been making money in her own way for so many years, it's probably her only survival skill.

She also cares about her friends in the way she's good at. I think aunt fraud must not have won my mother's money, because my mother said aunt aunt dimmy often said my mother played cards bad "mess. " . I think, as a cheater should generally hope that others can take advantage of their poor card skills, aunt Ding Mei scolded my mother poor skills, explained that she and her mother when playing cards is not as a cheater but as a friend.

Aunt Dingmei once invited her to join the cheating circle. At that time, my mother worked in the factory. Aunt Dingmei said, "you worked so hard to earn a little a month, and you could earn hundreds playing cards with me! " My Mother didn't go, and she stopped pushing. Sometimes aunt dimple would ask her acquaintances to play cards, and her mother would refuse, but this never affected their relationship.

My Dad says everyone knows she cheats. Who wants to play cards with her? My mother said yes, to the back can play cards less and less, some places play small (bet money less) , a handful of dozens of dollars she would also like to earn. I don't know if she's been doing her job in g city these past few years, bringing up her grandkids.

Screenshot of bird saint

Such a legend of a person, let a person more difficult to her and "jump off a building" , "think not to open" together. Is it the sickness or the isolation? My mother wondered if the family could also be infected can not accept, my father said maybe it is infected with the family in the heart of guilt? However, there are many cases of new coronary pneumonia cured, not infection is tantamount to death sentence, this explanation is difficult to make sense. My mother said that can infect the family daughter-in-law to say the bad word? When I say aunt dimmy doesn't sound like someone who cares very much about what people say about her?

But whatever the reason, it is the manager's responsibility to isolate the patient from suicide, so it was "expected" that no one would tell anyone, and in such a tense situation, such news would cause panic, with parents saying they "understand" and "should cooperate. ".

When I was doing the dishes, my mother came over to talk to me, and we talked a little bit more about aunt Dimmy, and my mother said that she was very bitter, and that she had a son and a daughter, and they were very smart, but in the'90s, my daughter died of leukemia. "Very smart girl. She's a teenager. She's doing well in school, " My mother said. "she must be very upset. "

But some of her acquaintances who knew she was out of fraud would say she had "Karma" for her daughter's death. I was so angry that I said, "it's a terrible thing, she couldn't have made a bigger mistake than her life, and it's a kick in the pants to curse someone when they're going through the worst of Bereavement! " My mother heard me say, just like the recognition of the same, just very confident to say: "Yes, is a rock under a rock! Otherwise so many sick people are also Karma? "

I suppose my mother, when she told her aunt dimmie's story, was afraid that we might judge her or speak ill of her, as we had done of all the acquaintances who had hated her, and that she might be as silent as ever. When she heard me say that these attacks were excessive, she felt secure in defending aunt dimmesdale. Mother got a recognition, and the story to the living room uncle and father, more firmly said: "These people are so vicious! " Uncle and said: "It is not right to say such words! "

In the afternoon, mom, dad and uncle played cards as usual. Dad Lost every time. This time, mom won the most. At Dinner, dad joked, "it's not your cheating friends who are protecting you! " I looked at mom, and she didn't say anything, and she didn't seem upset, but I couldn't help criticizing my father: "Aunt Dingmei has just passed away, it's so inappropriate to talk like that! " My mother just said to me: "Yes, isn't it disrespectful? " I criticized my father again, and my uncle also made some criticisms, my father just look at my mother, look at everyone, shut up and eat a few mouthfuls of rice.

It was probably the first time since aunt dimmie had died that her mother had expressed her feelings: it was her significant other who had died, and she was sorry for her. No one seemed to notice that the deceased was a close friend of MOM's, and everyone (including mom) talked about it as if it were gossip about someone else. The short visit lasted only a minute or two, and everyone went about their business again.

On March 2nd, it finally came out

On the third day, my mother told me that more people knew about aunt Dingmei's jumper, because some former classmates had come to tell her about it, someone asked her, "how could you not know? " Someone said, "it was her who jumped off the building in XX hotel. ". Another said, "I heard that whole family was infected... "

My Mom and dad talked about how she wouldn't be surprised if the whole family was infected. But I didn't think it was like aunt Dimmesdale in my mother's story. But who knows? People are many things, aren't they? Dad said, I heard that people are very uncomfortable with pneumonia, older body more unbearable, coupled with mental blows, may also have fragile time.

I asked. How could anyone know if it was a secret? Parents say that we all have acquaintances, each have their own sources of information, how to hide it? What had become of aunt dimmesdale's family, and how did they react to the news? I asked her family if they knew now?

My mother said she did not know, "I called her to turn off the phone" , "did not take a cell phone quarantine? No place to charge? " My mother could not help but wonder.

But when dad and uncle heard this, they scolded mom for not calling. Dad said if the phone was answered by a woman's Voice, would you be afraid (with a banter and superstition about ghosts and the like) , if the police got it, and find out you're digging into this, you're getting yourself in trouble. My mother argued that she had no contact information for her husband and no other way to ask about her family, but my father and uncle said not to call either. My Mom said it would never happen again.

But I thought, if I couldn't help but make a phone call, then a familiar person suddenly disappeared, and I couldn't ask or say if I had any questions or felt sad. Maybe the phone was the only one I could call, even though you know there's no answer, you still want to call, right? Is death and separation more cruel in themselves, or is it more cruel to have one's sorrow laid out?

I found my mother turning on an article called "friends are umbrellas in the rain" and writing, "in memory of my good friend / dimmy / also my classmate and best friend / MAY ALL BE WELL IN HEAVEN! "

Two days after the news of Aunt Dingmei's death, mother finally had no pressure to keep it a secret and could express her grief directly.

A way to mark the 3rd of March

On the fourth morning, I heard my mother singing in her room. My mother used to record songs at Karaoke in the whole country. She would share her works with her aunt and friends. She also had some singing equipment. But she hasn't been singing much lately, as if she didn't bring her gadgets.

However, my mother sang the same song over and over again, with some of the words sounding sad. I suppose mother wanted to sing it to aunt dimmy, to send a token of her affection.

Sure enough, at lunch my uncle teased my mother that she was in a good mood today. After singing songs all morning, my mother said that she was not in a good mood, but was remembering aunt Dingmei. "I was singing while my eyes were watering. " Mom sighed and said, "what can I do? There's no other way to remember it! " Yes, i really can't think of any other way.

My father and uncle told me about a man they knew died of pneumonia recently. "He was cremated the same day and buried the next day. Only his two sons went to the funeral. No one else could go. ". I asked. Doesn't his son have to be approved by the community to go to the funeral? Dad said, of course, no one can go out without a good reason.

I thought that even if aunt dimmy's family gave her a funeral, the friend of mother might not be able to attend it. Perhaps, as a matter of social convention, the immediate family of the deceased would have the priority of grief and would be the special case requiring proper care. Friends, on the other hand, may not be the kind of people who are allowed to attend a memorial service under martial law, or the kind of people around them who are supposed to be sensitive to grief.

The only time she could talk about her grief was this morning, when she was singing tearfully into her cell phone in a private room, the kind of ceremony she could think of to honor aunt dimmesdale.

It was as if the dust had settled, and the discussion of aunt Dimmesdale's death was no longer going on. After all, every day was a matter of when to break the seal and whether to buy the next meal or not.

It was only after lunch that my mother added, "I heard the hotel she was quarantining was very short. could she have fallen over the wall like all the other patients on the news? When we were kids, we climbed the wall together to steal firewood..."this was probably my mother's last guess as to the cause of aunt dimmy's death. "I still don't understand, " my mother said. I don't know, but maybe no one will.

I saw my mother posted in the friend circle of the work, just know her song is called "there is a missing called forever. ". My mother wrote: "My good friend! My good friend! My good classmate! May you live in peace in a faraway place! "

Aunt dimmy lived down the street from my grandmother and went to school with my mother, "the best of the best, " she added. She's also a bit of a legend, because she's a known cheater around here. My mother also explained that cheating is playing cards and other partners cheat and so on, I know that I heard right.

" My father and uncle listened and agreed.

When I was doing the dishes, my mother came over to talk to me, and we talked a little bit more about aunt Dimmy, and my mother said that she was very bitter, and that she had a son and a daughter, and they were very smart, but in the'90s, my daughter died of leukemia. In the afternoon, mom, dad and uncle played cards as usual. Dad Lost every time. This time, mom won the most. At Dinner, dad joked, "it's not your cheating friends who are protecting you! " I looked at mom, and she didn't say anything, and she didn't seem upset, but I couldn't help criticizing my father: "Aunt Dingmei has just passed away, it's so inappropriate to talk like that! " My mother just said to me: "Yes, isn't it disrespectful? " I criticized my father again, and my uncle also made some criticisms, my father just look at my mother, look at everyone, shut up and eat a few mouthfuls of rice.

It was probably the first time since aunt dimmie had died that her mother had expressed her feelings: it was her significant other who had died, and she was sorry for her. On March 2nd, it finally came out

On the third day, my mother told me that more people knew about aunt Dingmei's jumper, because some former classmates had come to tell her about it, someone asked her, "how could you not know? " Someone said, "it was her who jumped off the building in XX hotel. ". Another said, "I heard that whole family was infected... "

My Mom and dad talked about how she wouldn't be surprised if the whole family was infected. But I didn't think it was like aunt Dimmesdale in my mother's story. But who knows? People are many things, aren't they? Dad said, I heard that people are very uncomfortable with pneumonia, older body more unbearable, coupled with mental blows, may also have fragile time.

I asked. How could anyone know if it was a secret? Parents say that we all have acquaintances, each have their own sources of information, how to hide it? What had become of aunt dimmesdale's family, and how did they react to the news? I asked her family if they knew now?

My mother said she did not know, "I called her to turn off the phone" , "did not take a cell phone quarantine? No place to charge? " My mother could not help but wonder.

But when dad and uncle heard this, they scolded mom for not calling. Dad said if the phone was answered by a woman's Voice, would you be afraid (with a banter and superstition about ghosts and the like) , if the police got it, and find out you're digging into this, you're getting yourself in trouble. My mother argued that she had no contact information for her husband and no other way to ask about her family, but my father and uncle said not to call either. My Mom said it would never happen again.

But I thought, if I couldn't help but make a phone call, then a familiar person suddenly disappeared, and I couldn't ask or say if I had any questions or felt sad. Maybe the phone was the only one I could call, even though you know there's no answer, you still want to call, right? Is death and separation more cruel in themselves, or is it more cruel to have one's sorrow laid out?

A way to mark the 3rd of March

On the fourth morning, I heard my mother singing in her room. My mother used to record songs at Karaoke in the whole country. She would share her works with her aunt and friends. She also had some singing equipment. But she hasn't been singing much lately, as if she didn't bring her gadgets.

However, my mother sang the same song over and over again, with some of the words sounding sad. I suppose mother wanted to sing it to aunt dimmy, to send a token of her affection.

Sure enough, at lunch my uncle teased my mother that she was in a good mood today. After singing songs all morning, my mother said that she was not in a good mood, but was remembering aunt Dingmei. "I was singing while my eyes were watering. " Mom sighed and said, "what can I do? There's no other way to remember it! " Yes, i really can't think of any other way.

My father and uncle told me about a man they knew died of pneumonia recently. "He was cremated the same day and buried the next day. Only his two sons went to the funeral. No one else could go. ". I asked. Doesn't his son have to be approved by the community to go to the funeral? Dad said, of course, no one can go out without a good reason.

I thought that even if aunt dimmy's family gave her a funeral, the friend of mother might not be able to attend it. Perhaps, as a matter of social convention, the immediate family of the deceased would have the priority of grief and would be the special case requiring proper care. Friends, on the other hand, may not be the kind of people who are allowed to attend a memorial service under martial law, or the kind of people around them who are supposed to be sensitive to grief.

The only time she could talk about her grief was this morning, when she was singing tearfully into her cell phone in a private room, the kind of ceremony she could think of to honor aunt dimmesdale.
